## Integer ## 

String binary = Integer.toBinaryString(intNo) 
String hexString = Integer.toHexString(intNo)
String octString = Integer.toOctalString(intNo)
 
int bitCount = Integer.bitCount(intNo)   //return count of 1's in binary representation of intNo
int value = Integer.parseInt(binaryString, 2)     //binaryString e.g. 100, 1010




## Character ##

Character.isDigit(char)    => check if passed char is 0->9
Character.isLetter(char)   => check if input is letter (upper/lower case
Character.isLetterOrDigit(char) => checks for both mentioned above
Character.toUpperCase()
Character.toLowerCase()